main event: A person sighted a bright, self-luminous object that was rapidly moving and made a slow circling turn in the sky over Cassopolis, Michigan on 2/25/68 around 10:50 PM.
interesting points: The object appeared larger than a star and was described as 'self-luminous'.
The witness was walking from home to college when the object seemed to be following their walk back home.
The witness wanted to take a picture but their camera had no film.
The witness described the object as having an 'irregular shape' and a 'unique color'.
Other similar sightings were reported in the area around Cassopolis, Michigan.
sighted object: A bright, self-luminous object that made a slow circling turn
photographs: No, the report does not include any photographs
